The paper deals with learning algorithms for linear separators, which is a topic in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also provides new structural results for (nearly) log-concave distributions, which is a topic in probability theory and falls under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper uses information theory and communication complexity techniques, which are topics in cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also deals with active learning, which is a topic in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
